<F P=100> AUSTRALASIA </F>
<F P=101> Australia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Evans Approves Name Change of PLO Office </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2103093094 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0500 GMT 
21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2103093094 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Australia has approved a request to change the name 
of the Canberra office of the Palestine Liberation Organization. 
The title of the PLO office will be changed to the General 
Palestinian Delegation. 
  Announcing the move, Australia's foreign minister, Gareth 
Evans, said it did not involve any change in the diplomatic 
status of the PLO's representation. It did not involve the 
granting of any diplomatic privileges or immunities. 
  Senator Evans said conditions had not been satisfied for 
Australia to recognize Palestine as a sovereign state or the PLO 
as a government of a state. Australia's foreign minister has 
said the creation of an independent state of Palestine might 
well be the independent ultimate outcome of the peace process, 
but it was premature to anticipate the process at this stage. 

</TEXT>

