<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chongnyon Leader Addresses Japanese Party </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2003082794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0802 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2003082794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 18 (KNS-KCNA) [dateline as received] -- 
Ho Chong-man, chief vice-chairman of the Central Standing 
Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in 
Japan (Chongnyon), gave a lecture before officials of the Japan 
Social-Democratic Party on March 16 at a request of the party. 
  Present on the occasion were Secretary General Wataru Kubo 
and Vice-Chairman and concurrently International Department 
Director Issei Inoue of the party, Chairman of the Japan-Korea 
committee of the party and member of the House of 
Representatives Yuzuru Shimazaki and other Social-Democratic 
members of the House of Representatives and of the House of 
Councillors. 
  In his lecture the chief vice-chairman elaborated on the 
greatness of the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il and on the 
successful socialist construction in Korea under the wise 
guidance of the dear leader. 
  He said the DPRK would, in the future, too, adhere to the 
spirit of the three-party joint declaration on DPRK-Japan 
relations which was adopted between the Workers' Party of Korea, 
the Japan Liberal-Democratic Party and the Japan 
Social-Democratic Party in September 1990. 

</TEXT>

