<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tokyo Meeting of Korean Residents Held 18 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2203063894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0411 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2203063894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 19 (KNS-KCNA) [dateline as received] -- 
A central symposium of the General Association of Korean 
Residents in Japan (Chongnyon) was held at the Korea Hall in 
Tokyo on March 18 to learn from the greatness of the dear leader 
Marshal Kim Chong-il. 
  It was attended by vice-chairmen and department directors of 
the Central Standing Committee of Chongnyon, senior officials of 
organisations and enterprises and officials of propaganda, 
social science, the press, education, culture and art under 
Chongnyon. 
  Many people took the floor. 
  The speakers said the dear leader is a great thinker, 
theoretician, statesman and military strategist with literary 
and military accomplishments, a subject intensely loyal and 
filial to the great leader and a people's leader infinitely 
faithful to the country and the people. 
  In his address, Yi Chin-kyu, first vice-chairman of the 
Central Standing Committee of Chongnyon, stressed the need to 
strengthen Chongnyon to be a patriotic organisation faithful to 
the idea and leadership of Comrade Kim Chong-il, and expressed 
the belief that the participants would take the lead in making 
this year a year of education in his greatness. 
  A letter to Marshal Kim Chong-il was adopted at the 
symposium. 

</TEXT>

