<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cambodian Defense Ministry Delegation Visits </TI></H3>
<H4>   O Chin-u Hosts Banquet </H4>
<F P=102> SK2203064894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0451 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2203064894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["High-ranking Cambodian Defence Delegation Feted" -- KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 22 (KCNA) -- The Ministry of 
People's Armed Forces arranged a banquet at the Mansudae 
Assembly Hall on the evening of March 21 for the high-ranking 
delegation of the Ministry of Defence of the Royal Government of 
Cambodia headed by Co-Ministers of Defence General Tia Banh and 
General Tia Chambrat on a visit to Korea. 
  In his speech, Minister of People's Armed Forces O Chin-u 
said that the friendly relations between Korea and the Kingdom 
of Cambodia based on the particular and deep intimacy between 
the great leader Comrade Kim Il-song and esteemed His Majesty 
King Norodom Sihanouk are gaining greater scope and developing 
day by day. 
  He said that the royal government, the people and the 
officers and men of the Cambodian Army are registering 
remarkable achievements in the work to attain national 
reconciliation and unity and accelerate the reconstruction of 
the country, upholding the noble intention of esteemed His 
Majesty King Norodom Sihanouk. "Our people and the officers and 
men of the People's Army will as ever extend full support and 
firm solidarity to the fraternal people and officers and men of 
the army of Cambodia in their efforts for the independence and 
peace of the country, national unity and territorial integrity," 
declared O Chin-u. 
  Co-Minister of Defence Tea Chambrat spoke next. 
  He recalled that the friendship between the two countries 
based on the excellent relations of intimacy between His Majesty 
King Norodom Sihanouk and respected His Excellency Generalissimo 
Kim Il-song has a long history. 
  "The current visit of our high-ranking military delegation 
is 
aimed at demonstrating that we are always with Korea," he said. 
  He expressed the hope that the Korean people would enjoy a 
greater happiness. 

</TEXT>

