<H3> <TI>   Moscow Marks Anniversary of DPRK-Russia Accord </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2003080194 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 0700 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2003080194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 0700 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A meeting to mark the 45th anniversary of the 
signing of the agreement on economic and cultural cooperation 
between the DPRK and the Russian Federation was held in Moscow 
on 17 March. [sentence as heard] 
  Present at the gathering were (Vladimir Torsikov,) chairman 
of the central council of the Russian society for friendship and 
cultural cooperation with the DPRK; vice chairmen; Yi Tong-chol, 
chairman of the united association of Korean people in Russia; 
functionaries of the Eastern Affairs Research Institute of the 
Academy of Science; war veterans, and Koreans residing in Moscow. 
  Son Song-pil, ambassador of our country to Russia, and 
members of the DPRK Embassy staff were invited. 
  Speeches were delivered at the meeting. The speakers said 
the 
agreement on economic and cultural cooperation between the DPRK 
and Russia was concluded on the basis of the principle of 
complete equality and that this agreement opened the beginning 
of the development of cooperation between the two countries and 
peoples. 
  Pointing out the achievements made by our people in the past 
in the fields of industry, agriculture, science, education, 
public health, literature, and art, they said that the Korean 
people are brilliantly implementing the gigantic social and 
economic tasks put forward by the Workers Party of Korea. 
  They stressed that the DPRK has become a model of socialist 
countries. 

</TEXT>

