<F P=100> SOUTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Burma </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Officers Groomed for Future Leadership </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2103150294 Rangoon Radio Burma in Burmese 1330 GMT 21 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2103150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rangoon Radio Burma </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Burmese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Senior General Than Shwe, chairman of the State Law 
and Order Restoration Council [SLORC] and commander in chief of 
the defense services, attended and delivered an address at the 
inauguration of National Defense College [NDC] Training Course 
No. 1 held at the Anawrahta Hall of the NDC at Konemyinttha in 
Yangon [Rangoon] at 0900. 
  The ceremony was attended by Lieutenant General Maung Aye, 
deputy commander in chief of the defense services and army 
commander in chief; Vice Admiral Maung Maung Khin and Lt. Gen. 
Tin Tun, both SLORC members and deputy prime ministers; Lt. Gen. 
Tin U, SLORC secretary-2; SLORC members; cabinet ministers; the 
chief justice; the attorney general; Yangon city development 
committee chairman and mayor; senior military officials; NDC 
principal and lecturers; rectors from the universities; invited 
guests; and trainees. 
  SLORC Chairman Sr. Gen. Than Shwe noted that the NDC's 
Training Course No. 1, which opened today, is the first of its 
kind to be held in Myanmar [Burma] and the training is intended 
to nurture reliable and qualified leaders for the country. He 
expressed the need for the trainees to be diligent in their 
training and to implement the experiences gained from the course 
for the betterment of the country. 
  Sr. Gen. Than Shwe then cordially greeted the trainees and 
departed at 1030. 

</TEXT>

