<F P=100> Brunei, Malaysia &amp; Singapore </F>
<F P=101> Singapore </F>
<H3> <TI>   Badawi on Regional Security, Growth Triangle </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2203123694 Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation in 
English 1100 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2203123694 </F>
<F P=104>  Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Malaysia's foreign minister said he would like to 
see more contacts with Singapore at a younger level. Mr. 
Abdullah Ahmad Badawi, who is in Singapore on a two-day visit, 
said bilateral relations are good and there is very [as heard] 
contact at the ministers' level. But he said there is a need to 
replace the old schoolboy network forged through the Raffles 
College link. Mr. Abdullah was speaking in an informal dialogue 
session with young PAP [People's Action Party] members. 
  At a news conference this afternoon, Mr. Abdullah said that 
the ASEAN regional forum on security and the need to ensure its 
success was a topic discussed by Singapore leaders. 
  On the growth triangle, the foreign minister said the 
discussions touched on the need to have an easy flow of labor 
among the three countries in the group. Mr. Abdullah said the 
three should maximize their advantages in labor resources on a 
project basis. 

</TEXT>

