<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Seoul Urges DPRK To Fulfill Nuclear Obligation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2203001994 Seoul YONHAP in English 0005 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2203001994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, March 22 (YONHAP) -- Seoul demanded Monday 
that Pyongyang fulfill its nuclear safeguards obligations and 
clear up suspicions about its nuclear program, calling attention 
to the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) resolution. 
  The South Korean Government noted the March 21 resolution 
adopted by an absolute majority and saw it as a reflection of 
the international community's will, Chang Ki-ho, Foreign 
Ministry spokesman, said in a statement. 
  "It's a reflection of the suspicion and concern of the 
international community regarding North Korea's nuclear 
development caused by North Korea's refusal to fulfill its 
responsibilities and obligations despite global efforts over the 
past year," the statement said. 
  "The government urges that North Korea completely implement 
all its safeguards obligations and clear up global suspicion 
about its nuclear development," it said. 

</TEXT>

