<F P=103> SK2203025794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul CHOSON ILBO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] It has been learned on 21 March that North Korea 
recently sent a letter to the U.S. Government through channels 
in New York warning that if the United States does not withdraw 
its demands for additional International Atomic Energy Agency 
inspections and the exchange of North and South Korean special 
envoys as the precondition of the third round of the North 
Korea- U.S. talks, North Korea could stop operating various 
surveillance equipment installed in Yongbyon's nuclear 
facilities. 

