<H3> <TI>   President Kim Urges Full Security Preparedness </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2203104294 Seoul YONHAP in English 1032 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2203104294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, March 22 (YONHAP) -- President Kim Yong-sam 
called upon the Armed Forces to maintain watertight vigilance 
against North Korea on Tuesday, two days before his scheduled 
official visit to Japan. 
  Kim made the call during a luncheon he hosted at Chongwadae 
[presidential office] for top military leaders. 
  Those invited to the lunch included Defense Minister Yi 
Pyong-tae, Joint Chiefs of Staff Chairman Yi Yang-ho, Army Chief 
of Staff Kim Tong-chin, Chief of Naval Operations Kim Hong-yol 
and Air Force Chief of Staff Kim Hong-nae. 
  The president asked the attendees to prepare fully against 
any contingency by bolstering defense preparedness and 
maintaining close cooperative system with allies, a Chongwadae 
source said. 

