<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Joint Chiefs of Staff Order `Special Alert' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2203122894 Seoul YONHAP in English 1218 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2203122894 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, March 22 (YONHAP) -- The Joint Chiefs of 
Staff on Tuesday ordered the whole South Korean Armed Forces to 
be on a special alert from March 23 through March 30. 
  During the alert, all major commanders and staff officers 
should stand by within easy access to communications, and leaves 
and outings of all officers and men will be controlled. 
  An officer said the alert is to ensure firmer security 
preparedness as President Kim Yong-sam, the supreme military 
commander, is making an overseas tour at a time when a tension 
is building up on the Korean peninsula following the breakup of 
Panmunjom talks. 
  President Kim leaves the country on March 24 to embark on an 
official visit to Japan, which will be followed by his tour of 
China. 
  "Apart from the special alert, the special military 
preparedness order issued earlier for a period until the end of 
this month, will be extended for the time being," the officer 
said. 

</TEXT>

