<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Party Leaders Postpone Visit to Europe </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2103115294 Seoul YONHAP in English 1139 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2103115294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, March 21 (YONHAP) -- The floor leaders of the 
ruling Democratic Liberal Party [DLP] and opposition Democratic 
Party [DP] on Monday put off indefinitely their planned visit to 
Europe due to strained situation at home over the breakup of the 
South-North talks. 
  Reps. Yi Han-tong of the DLP and Kim Tae-sik of the DP 
earlier planned to visit eight European countries for two weeks 
beginning March 22. They were to be accompanied by two other 
solons. 
  Yi told reporters that he met the opposition floor leader 
earlier in the day and agreed to put off their visit until a 
later date due to the tense situation. 
  "If and when the situation calms down, we will try to make 
the visit for about ten days," Yi added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

