<H3> <TI>   Le Kha Phieu Attends Military Congress in Vinh </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1903093594 Hanoi Vietnam Television Network in Vietnamese 
1215 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1903093594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Vietnam Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Vietnamese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Recently, the 4th Military Region party committee 
held a mid-term party congress in the city of Vinh in Nghe An 
Province with 108 delegates representing thousands of party 
members in the military region. Senior Lieutenant General Le 
Kha Phieu, member of the Political Bureau, secretary of the 
Central Committee, and director of the Political General 
Department of the Vietnam People's Army, attended the congress 
on behalf of the Military Central Committee. 
  The report of the 4th Military Region party committee 
carefully reviewed work performance during the last two years. 
The committee has sufficiently improved its national defense 
performance in the region, contributing to the political 
stabilization and socioeconomic development and national 
protection. The congress also mentioned duties in the near 
future and pledged to accomplish all requirements set forth by 
the all-army party congress. 
  Senior Lieut. Gen. Le Kha Phieu hailed achievements by the 
party committees and forces in the 4th Military Region. He also 
outlined key directions for the congress to study and discuss. 

