<H3> <TI>   Agreement Reached With U.S. on Helicopter Deal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2203091794 Tokyo KYODO in English 0856 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2203091794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 22 KYODO -- Japan has agreed with the 
United States to continue producing under license UH-60J combat 
search and rescue helicopters, the Foreign Ministry said Tuesday 
[22 March]. The ministry said the diplomatic notes relating to 
the accord were exchanged earlier in the day between Foreign 
Minister Tsutomu Hata and U.S. Ambassador to Japan Walter 
Mondale. 
  The utility helicopters will be produced by Mitsubishi Heavy 
Industries Ltd. for the Maritime Self-Defense Force (MSDF) and 
the Air Self-Defense Force (ASDF), which have plans to add three 
more to their helicopter fleets by April 1996. 

