<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Welcomes El Salvador Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2203084294 Tokyo KYODO in English 0810 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2203084294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 22 KYODO -- Japan welcomed Tuesday [22 
March] the peaceful general elections held in El Salvador on 
Sunday, saying it was a major turning point for the peace 
process of the Latin American country. 
  Foreign Ministry spokesman Terusuke Terada said Japan 
welcomes the elections held "without turmoil or political 
terrorism" and that it hopes the elections will serve to advance 
the peace process there. 
  Fifteen Japanese election observers took part in monitoring 
the voting and ballot counting. They are scheduled to return to 
Japan on Friday. 

