<H3> <TI>   Government To Draw Up 50-Day Provisional Budget </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2203054394 Tokyo KYODO in English 0524 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2203054394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 22 KYODO -- The government agreed 
Tuesday [22 March] to draw up a provisional draft budget for the 
first 50 days of the new fiscal year starting April 1, 
government sources said. The agreement was reached in a 
high-level meeting of coalition parties and the government 
following a proposal by Finance Minister Hirohisa Fujii. 
  The provisional budget, covering the period to May 20, will 
amount to 11 trillion yen, the biggest ever, covering personnel 
expenditure and public works programs, the sources said. 

