<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRC To Cooperate in Civil Cases, Arbitration </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2203052394 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in English 0000 
GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2203052394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Thailand and China have agreed on cooperation with 
civil lawsuits and arbitration between the two countries. 
Minister of Justice Sawai Phatthano says he had reached the 
agreement with his Chinese counterpart during his recent visit 
to China. Minister Sawai says according to the agreement, Thai 
nationals in China will be under the justice authority 
designated under the same category and at the same level as the 
Chinese authority. In addition, Thai nationals in China will 
now have the right to fight a lawsuit against individuals in 
China. 
  He says Thailand is the 18th country to sign such an 
agreement with China. Earlier Thailand and China have signed an 
extradition agreement. The minister says he and his Chinese 
counterpart have agreed to promote arbitration as a means to 
settle disputes over marine trade and transportation between the 
countries. The minister of justice says that for the 19 years 
of Thai-Chinese diplomatic relations, their cooperation in laws 
should be made to support other ties. 

</TEXT>

