<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hungary Requests Commercial Banks To Invest </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2103045694 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in English 0000 
GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2103045694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hungary has urged Thai commercial banks to open 
their representative offices or invest in setting up commercial 
banks in that country. 
  According to the Department of Information, Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs, to invest in setting up a bank in Hungary 
requires a capital of at least U.S. $10 million. Hungary agreed 
to consider easing various constraints to pave the way for the 
setting up of branch offices in Hungary by Thai commercial 
banks. The country also wants to sell several industrial 
products to Thailand, such as railway tracks, crop godowns, and 
cooling system cables. Thailand asked Hungary to buy more Thai 
products in return. 
  During the recent visit to Hungary by Deputy Prime Minister 
Suphachai Phanitchaphak, Thailand proposed that Hungary use 
tapioca as an ingredient for animal feed production. Hungary 
asked Thailand's advice for the use of tapioca in animal feed 
production. The country also agreed to serve as an agent to 
bring frozen pork from Thailand for further distribution to the 
commonwealth independent state. 

</TEXT>

