<H3> <TI>   Decree Convenes Special Assembly Session </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2203081994 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in Thai 0530 GMT 
22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2203081994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Thai </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] His Royal Signature, given on 19 March 1994, being 
the 49th year under his reign, 
  His Majesty King Phumiphon Adunyadet has commanded that it 
be 
announced that for the interests of the state it is deemed 
necessary and appropriate to convene an extraordinary session of 
the Parliament. Therefore, empowered by Articles 130, 132, and 
175 of the Constitution of the Kingdom of Thailand, he has 
graciously issued a decree to convene the extraordinary 
parliamentary session from 31 March 1994. 
  Countersigned by Prime Minister Chuan Likphai 

</TEXT>

