<F P=100> Brunei, Malaysia &amp; Singapore </F>
<F P=101> Malaysia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mahathir Urges `Informal' APEC Meetings </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2203094894 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0800 
GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2203094894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Datuk Sri Dr. Mahathir Mohamed says he will attend 
the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation, APEC, informal summit in 
Jakarta in November, and again stressed the need for the forum 
not to be institutionalized. 
  The prime minister, who skipped the first meeting in Seattle 
last year and caused dissatisfaction among some APEC members, 
said he would be attending the summit since it was decided by 
APEC. The inaugural summmit held in Seattle was initiated by 
United States President Bill Clinton. 
  Speaking at the press conference after delivering a keynote 
address at the 10th International General Meeting of the Pacific 
Economic Cooperation Council in Kuala Lumpur, Datuk Sri Dr. 
Mahathir reiterated that APEC should conduct informal meetings. 
The prime minister said APEC should continue to exist as an 
informal meeting and should not institutionalized its meetings 
and have regular programs for a smooth [word indistinct]. But 
the forum should not bind its members and that these objectives 
should seek for members to know each other and understand their 
constructive point of views. 
  To a question, Datuk Sri Dr. Mahathir said the 
Malaysian-initiated East Asia Economic Caucus, EAEC, is not 
institutionalized and that it is a forum to discuss common 
problems among countries in the region. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

