<H3> <TI>   Effect of DPRK Sanctions on Ethnic Koreans </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2203053094 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 22 
Mar 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2203053094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 22 Mar Evening Edition] </F>
  [Text] A government source said on the morning of 22 March 
that if the UN Security Council decides to slap economic 
sanctions on North Korea in connection with its suspected 
nuclear weapons development, "it would be difficult" for the 
Japanese Government to ban the remittance of money by ethnic 
Koreans in Japan to North Korea. But he stressed that the 
"Japanese Government should make every possible effort to stop 
the ethnic Koreans from remitting money to North Korea if the UN 
Security Council imposes the economic sanctions on North Korea." 

</TEXT>

