<H3> <TI>   MONTSAME Reviews Press for 22 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2203140794 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1216 GMT 22 Mar 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2203140794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, March 22 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The central 
newspaper "ARDIYN ERH" informs that the State Great Hural spring 
session finished consideration of the draft law on currency. 
The draft law was adopted by the majority of votes and it was 
decided to call it as the law on regulation of currency. The 
law will come into force from 1 May. At the same time adopted 
was the resolution of the State Great Hural on measures on 
realization of this law. At the yesterday's sitting of the 
State Great Hural, consideration of the issue about making 
amendments and additions in the law on elections began. This 
issue has been submitted to the parliament by the President of 
Mongolia P. Ochirbat. The newspaper informs that the Mongolian 
delegation headed by the vice-chairman of the State Great Hural, 
deputy chairman of the Mongolian parliamentary group J. Gombojab 
has left Ulaanbaatar for Paris to attend the regular conference 
of the Interparliamentary Union. The newspaper informs also 
that the Vice-Premier of Mongolia L. Enebish left on a visit to 
Hungary, Czechia and Belgium. L. Enebish is planning to get 
acquainted with the experience of the above-mentioned countries 
in the sphere of state governing and market relations. 
  The newspaper carries an interview of its correspondent with 
the deputy chairman of the standing emergency commission 
Major-General G. Damdinsuren about the situation in 
animal-husbandry. G. Damdinsuren points out to difficult 
weather conditions in Tub Aymag, where there was a heavy 
snow-fall. As G. Damdinsuren notes there will be great 
difficulties in breeding cattle this spring. 
  The newspaper publishes an article by the State Great Hural 
member T. Turmandah apropos of the statements made by the 
representatives of the opposition parties in the parliament, 
concerning involvement of some members of the state leadership 
in corruption. T. Turmandah considers these accusations as 
groundless. 
  The newspaper "HUMUUN BICHIG," which is issued by the 
MONTSAME agency in the old Mongolian script informs about the 
sitting of the state commission on preparation for introduction 
of the traditional Mongolian script in official clerical work. 
In the information it is noted that the Mongolian script will 
be used in clerical work and official correspondence from 1995. 
  The newspaper acquaints the readers with reacclimatization 
of 
wild horses-tahi in the primordial places of their inhabitance. 
Wild horse-tahi is at present only in zoological gardens of 
foreign countries. These countries have sent to Mongolia about 
20 wild horses, which are being acclimatized in the Gobi regions 
of the country. 
  The newspaper continues publishing the exercises for those 
learning the old Mongolian script, texts for reading. 

</TEXT>

