<H3> <TI>   Italians Sign Economic Cooperation Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR2103151394 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 0930 GMT 21 
Mar 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2103151394 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Thailand/Italy: Confindustria </F>
Forges Accord"] 
  [Text] Bangkok, 21 Mar (ANSA) -- In the course of a visit 
here, the head of a CONFINDUSTRIA [General Confederation of 
Italian Industry] delegation (of Italian industrialists), 
Rosolino Orlando signed an accord for economic, industrial and 
technological cooperation with the Federation of Thai Industries. 
  Orlando said over the weekend that he envisaged immediate 
forms of cooperation in the fields of food, machine tools, 
metalworking and woodworking. Thai industrialists will be 
taking part in Italian trade fairs and will make use of Italy's 
experience in professional training at intermediate levels. 
  During his visit, Orlando met with Thai business leaders and 
with the deputy ministers for foreign trade and for industry. 
The CONFINDUSTRIA delegation included bankers as well as 
industrialists. 
  Italian exports to Thailand markedly increased in 1993, 
reaching the sum of 1.4 trillion lire (833 million dollars). 
Furthermore, the direct presence of Italian industry in the 
fields of steel, energy, installations and construction has 
deepened. 
  In fact, Thailand is ever more strongly seen as a focal 
point 
of growing importance in terms of Italian economic activities 
towards Indochina. 

</TEXT>

