<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ninety-Nine Percent of Spring Crop Complete </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2203075394 Hanoi VNA in English 0622 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2203075394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA March 22 -- By mid-March, the whole 
country had cropped 232,260 ha with winter-spring rice, 
accounting for nearly 99 percent of the plan. In general the 
paddy is growing well. Meanwhile the southern provinces had 
harvested 540,140 ha of early winter-spring rice. According to 
initial reports, the Mekong River delta achieved a yield of 4-6 
tons/ha. 

