<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hayashi Says No Surprises in Economic Package </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2403044094 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 24 
Mar 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2403044094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 24 March Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] Sadayuki Hayashi, newly named deputy vice minister 
of foreign affairs (in charge of economic issues), granted an 
interview to a NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN reporter on 23 March. In 
the interview, Hayashi touched on a package of external economic 
measures to be compiled by the government by the end of this 
month, and said: "It is difficult to come up with macro 
economic measures because there are various limitations in this 
field. I do not think surprising measures will be included in 
the package." Thus he indicated that, this time, the government 
would not spell out drastic measures such as a plan to continue 
tax cuts from 1995 onward. Regarding the resumption of 
Japan-U.S. economic framework talks, Hayashi said: "It seems to 
be difficult." 

</TEXT>

