<F P=101> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commercial Banks Report Credits, Interest Rates </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2303172394 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1532 GMT 23 Mar 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2303172394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, March 23 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
monthly of credits interests of commercial banks directed to 
development of the sector of small and medium enterprises 
constitute for the present 8-15 percent, which is by almost 10 
percent lower than in the last year. 15 commercial banks of 
Mongolia by the beginning of March have granted to economic 
units credits worth 39 billion tugriks, which is by 2.4 percent 
higher than in February. The credits to economic units and 
enterprises of the state sector constituted 15 billion tugriks, 
or by 12 percent lower then in the last months. The credits to 
the private sector have increased and constituted 23 billion 
tugriks. 

</TEXT>

