<F P=100> SOUTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Burma </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mine Injures Villager in Kayikto </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2303151894 Rangoon Radio Burma in Burmese 1300 GMT 23 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2303151894 </F>
<F P=104>  Rangoon Radio Burma </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Burmese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Members of the armed organizations in the jungle 
have been laying mines on railway lines, roads, and sidewalks 
with the intent to destroy them and to kill and maim the people 
who want to live peacefully. They are also hindering and 
disturbing smooth and secure transportation as well as local 
tranquility. 
  At about 1600 on 2 March, Maung Tar Htay, the 19-year-old 
son 
of U Aye Myint Lwin of the village of Kyaukpya, Kyaikto 
Township, stepped on an antipersonnel mine laid by members of 
the Karen armed organization in the jungle while he was 
returning to Kyaukpya from the fields. He lost his toes in the 
accident. The responsible personnel took him to Kyaikto 
Hospital for treatment. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

