<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Patriot Deployment Termed `Extremely Agitating' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2403060394 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2200 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2403060394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2200 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to reports, the United States is 
deliberately driving the situation of the Korean peninsula to a 
war phase [kyehoekchoguro chosonbandoui chongserul chonjaeng 
kungmyonero moragago issumnida] after rupturing the DPRK-U.S. 
talks. 
  As has been learned, the United States completely turned 
over 
[chonmyon twijibo opko] the agreement reached at the New York 
DPRK-U.S. contact and broke up [patansikigo] the third round of 
the DPRK-U.S. talks. Nevertheless, the United States poses open 
[nogolhwa] military threats and pressure against us under unjust 
pretexts, shifting the responsibility for the rupture of the 
talks to us. 
  U.S. President Clinton made a very provocative order [maeu 
tobalchogin myongnyong] to deploy 192 Patriot missiles in South 
Korea as soon as the DPRK-U.S. talks came to a rupture, as 
though he had been waiting for it. 
  The U.S. Department of Defense said that a Patriot missile 
battalion with some 40 missile launching ramps and 850 soldiers 
was going to move from Texas, the United States, to South Korea, 
according to the order. The U.S. measure of deploying Patriot 
missiles in South Korea is threatening and extremely agitating 
[simhi chaguk]. It is a kind of declaration of overall 
confrontation with us [urie taehan ilchongui chonmyon taegyol 
sonon], a declaration of war. 
  According to the U.S. newspaper WASHINGTON POST dated 22 
March, the U.S. Administration is plotting a scheme to take 
next-stage military steps against us [urirul pandaehanun taum 
tangyeui kunsajok chochidurul chwiharyogo hoekchukhago 
issumnida]. 
  Following the decision to deploy Patriot missiles, the U.S. 
Administration is trying to dispatch additional U.S. military 
forces to South Korea, to move and deploy U.S. aircraft carriers 
along the coastline of the Korean peninsula, and to arm the U.S. 
Forces in South Korea and the South Korean puppet Army with new 
military equipment. 
  The British newspaper EVENING STANDARD reported that a U.S. 
naval fleet with 30 naval vessels was approaching an area where 
it can reach our country's coast in 24 hours. This fleet has 
two mobile aircraft carrier units and landing operations forces, 
including the Marine Corps, aboard. 
  According to Japan's MAINICHI SHIMBUN dated 19 March, the 
U.S. nuclear-powered aircraft carrier Carl Vinson lately 
departed from Japan's Yokosuka Port with six escort ships and is 
maintaining a mobile posture heading toward the Korean peninsula. 
  Prior to this, the U.S. aircraft carrier Independence led by 
the Mobile Bay, an Aegis missile cruiser; (?Bainbridge), a 
guided missile cruiser; and two frigates had called at Port 
Yokosuka. They are also preparing against a possible case by 
standing by within the reach of the Korean peninsula. 
  Meanwhile, the U.S. warmongers are openly disclosing its 
plot 
to resume the Team Spirit nuclear war exercise, and the 
bellicose remarks on the Team Spirit continue to resound from 
the Congress. 
  The Democratic whip leader in the House of Representatives 
and the Republican whip leader in the Senate, in an interview 
with NBC Television, raved that the United States should resume 
the Team Spirit joint military exercise so as to impose pressure 
on North Korea by actually carrying it out. 
  We cannot but say such ill-boding military moves, containing 
the danger of a war provocation, will only bring out vigilance 
[undanghan kyonggaesim]. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

