<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Outbursts of U.S. War-Thirsty Elements" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 24 (KCNA) -- High-placed 
politicians of the United States are now getting frenzied in the 
kickup for pressure on the Democratic People's Republic of 
Korea, according to a report from Washington. 
  Democratic leader of whip in the House of Representatives 
Richard Gephardt said the United States must deploy Patriot 
missiles in South Korea, resume the "Team Spirit" nuclear war 
exercises and additionally dispatch U.S. troops to South Korea. 
Republican leader of whip in the Senate Robert Dole also made 
such remarks, crying for "a deliberation of economic sanctions 
against North Korea." 
  Meanwhile, U.S. State Secretary Christopher, in his 
interview 
with CBS, openly revealed the intention to put pressure on the 
DPRK by abusing "a resolution of the United Nations" and thus 
bring the situation of the Korean peninsula to a hopeless phase. 
  All this clearly indicates that the U.S. hardline 
conservatives are invariably pursuing the reckless policy of 
isolating and stifling the DPRK. 
  Any pressure and sanctions, however, can never work with the 
DPRK. The Korean people value peace. But, they will not 
tolerate anyone who dares infringe upon the nation's sovereignty 
and dignity. 
  The U.S. war-thirsty elements would be well advised to stop 
running rashly, clearly knowing of the DPRK where the leader, 
the party and the popular masses are united in one mind. 

</TEXT>

