<H3> <TI>   Daily Denounces U.S. for `Nuclear Blackmail' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2403105294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1023 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2403105294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["MINJU CHOSON Slams Nuclear Threat of U.S. Military"--KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 24 (KCNA) -- The U.S. military 
recently discussed the "possibility of the use of nuclear 
weapons" allegedly to "check" the chemical and biological weapon 
"attack" from non-nuclear states. 
  Branding this as an unpardonable crime, a MINJU CHOSON 
analyst today says: 
  The open argument for the "possibility of the use of nuclear 
weapons" by the U.S. military contradicts the principle of the 
Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty (NPT). 
  The NPT itself is an inequitable treaty favorable only for 
the nuclear-weapon states. Moreover, the United States, a 
nuclear power, is presenting nuclear threat to non-nuclear 
states, frequently violating the NPT, which it signed. 
  Its nuclear threat still remains and is getting more 
undisguised today after the end of the Cold War, not to speak of 
the Cold War era. 
  The United States is intensifying nuclear threat to the 
DPRK, 
a non-nuclear and peaceful state. Although the United States in 
its joint statement with the DPRK in June last year committed 
itself not to use force of arms including nuclear weapons or 
pose a threat, it has never ceased nuclear blackmail to the DPRK 
with nuclear war exercises targeted against it. 
  The U.S. is increasing its nuclear threat to the DPRK by 
manipulating even the International Atomic Energy Agency. It 
has reversed the agreed conclusions reached at the DPRK-U.S. 
contact in New York and is going to stage the Team Spirit 94 
joint military maneuvers, a nuclear war game against the DPRK. 
  The United States is a nuclear war criminal who has already 
imposed nuclear disaster on humanity. 
  The United States must clearly see the demand of the times 
and the desire of the world people and act with discretion. 

</TEXT>

