<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Tension Further Strained" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 24 (KCNA) -- Some 400 Japan-based 
U.S. fighters and fighter-bombers, assault planes, observation 
planes and reconnaissance planes of the U.S. Airforce present in 
South Korea and the South Korean puppet airforce staged 
provocative joint air war exercises in the sky above Chunchon, 
Pyongchang, Yongwol and Kongju of South Korea on March 21 and 
22, according to military sources. 
  Meanwhile, the South Korean puppet army on the same days 
fired more than 50 shells with tank guns at the area near the 
demilitarized zone from Paju county, and on the 22d fired some 
2,000 bullets with large-calibre machine-guns and automation 
rifles, advancing towards the Military Demarcation Line from 
Paju County and Yonchon County. 
  They launched exercises for surprise strike at the targets 
and disturbance in the rear, repeatedly dropping "commandoes" in 
Paju county on March 21 and 22. 
  The tension on the Korean peninsula is being screwed up by 
the war provocative moves of the U.S. imperialists and the South 
Korean puppets at a time when the schemes for "sanctions" 
against the DPRK are being hatched up in the arena of the United 
Nations and the U.S. aggression forces are moving towards the 
Korean peninsula from the U.S. mainland and U.S. military bases 
in the Pacific region. 

</TEXT>

