<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Soldiers Returning From South Given Awards </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2303153194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1504 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2303153194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 23 (KCNA) -- The Central People's 
Committee of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea recently 
awarded the title of Hero of the Republic to Kim Chol-chin (23), 
a non-commissioned officer of the Korean People's Security 
Forces (KPSF), and the "Kim Il-song Youth Honor Prize" to Kim 
Kyong-chol (20), a KPSF soldier, who have come back home in 
triumph by fighting it out with a rock-firm faith and principles 
as People's Army soldiers, not yielding to the enemy when they 
were taken [word indistinct] South Korea under unavoidable 
circumstances. 
  At the end of January, they were arrested by the South 
Korean 
authorities in distress in the West Sea while on military duty. 
  The enemy employed all conceivable moves to convert the two 
soldiers. 
  The enemy put them each in a solitary cell, allured them 
with 
money and goods, sent in turncoats to win them over and 
threatened them, showing them bloody torture rooms. 
  The enemy, however, could not break the revolutionary 
constancy and will of the KPSF soldiers who have had iron faith. 
  Although they were detained by the enemy, they resolutely 
fought the enemy with a dignified attitude as soldiers of 
Comrade Kim Chong-il, the supreme commander, believing him only 
and sent tremor through the enemy, before coming back to the 
bosom of the socialist homeland, the bosom of General Kim 
Chong-il. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

