<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Japanese Defense Agency Chief's Remarks Decried </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2403050894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0455 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2403050894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Indiscreet Preach of Aggression" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 24 (KCNA) -- Kazuo Aichi, general 
director of the Defence Agency of Japan, at the commencement of 
the "Defence Academy" a few days ago said "international 
contribution" is an important duty of the "self-defence forces" 
(SDF) and that the role of the "SDF" is increasing in the 
"contribution" through the United Nations. He also talked about 
the "responsibility" of the "SDF." 
  This revealed the sinister intention of the Japanese 
reactionaries to drive the "SDF" into overseas aggression, 
declares NODONG SINMUN today. 
  The news analyst says: 
  The "international contribution" of the "SDF" claimed by the 
Japanese reactionary ruling quarters is an excuse to justify 
troop dispatch overseas and the use of arms. 
  By "increasing role" of the "SDF" through the United 
Nations, 
aichi meant to step up its military advance and operations 
overseas by abusing the name of the United Nations. 
  The Japanese reactionaries are these days preaching the 
inevitability of the use of weapons and battles of the "SDF" 
units dispatched overseas and calling for malrevision of the 
"law on cooperation in UN peacekeeping operations," which 
confines their activities to non-military spheres, and for the 
"constitutionality" of "military activities under UN command" 
and "exercise of the right to collective self-defence." Under 
the cloak of "exercise of the right to collective self-defence" 
they intend to start military aggression in real earnest on 
wider areas, major zones of resources and strategic points of 
the world. 
  Japan today is the world's number two in military spendings. 
  What must not go unnoticed is that the Japanese reactionary 
ruling quarters are actively promoting Japan's nuclear armament. 
  The Japanese reactionaries must discard the anachronistic 
militarist mode of thinking and act with discretion. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

