<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Japanese Reported Protesting Kim Yong-sam Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2403115494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1015 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2403115494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 22 (KNS-KCNA) -- The Japanese people 
are protesting Kim Yong-sam's tour of their country. 
  Genzu Watanabe, secretary of the Japan-South Korea Council 
of 
People's Solidarity, made a report and public figures speeches 
at a meeting held in Tokyo on March 17. 
  They pointed out that the criminal purpose of the tour of 
Japan by the traitor Kim Yong-sam is to strengthen the 
Japanese-South Korean joint step against the DPRK, promote 
political conspiracy regarding the past Japan's aggression on 
Korea and colonial rule and build new relations between Japan 
and South Korea. 
  They called upon the Japanese people to obtain a clear 
understanding of the essence of Kim Yong-sam's tour of Japan, 
strengthen solidarity with the South Korean people struggling 
for independence, democracy and peaceful reunification and wage 
a vigorous struggle in demand of a fundamental switchover of the 
Japan government's policy towards Korea. 

</TEXT>

