<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Peng's Remarks on DPRK Nuclear Issue Cited </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2403043994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0415 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2403043994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pressure Will Only Make Situation on Korean Peninsula </F>
Tense" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 24 (KCNA) -- Chinese Premier Li 
Peng told Chinese and foreign reporters on March 22 that it has 
been China's consistent position to stand for negotiations and 
dialogues rather than pressure on the issue of nuclear 
inspection in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, XINHUA 
reported. 
  Answering a question by a reporter on China's stand if the 
issue is submitted to the Security Council of the United 
Nations, the premier said that if the method of pressure is 
used, it will only make things more complicated, and make the 
situation on the Korean peninsula tense, and that will not be 
good for the peace and stability of the region. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

