<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guyana, Brazil Parties Denounce U.S. `Attitude' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2303151094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1500 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2303151094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 23 (KCNA) -- Political parties and 
organizations of Guyana and Brazil denounced the U.S. insincere 
attitude toward the talks between the Democratic People's 
Republic of Korea and the United States. 
  Fourteen political parties and organizations of Guyana 
including the People's Democratic Movement, the Amerindian 
Action Movement, the Agricultural and General Workers Union and 
the Guyana-Korea Friendship Association released a statement on 
March 7 saying that no problem could be solved in such a manner 
as putting pressure on one side or setting unreasonable 
preconditions. It stressed that the United States must come out 
to the talks without any precondition and fully discharge its 
responsibility and obligation in the solution to the nuclear 
issue on the Korean peninsula. 
  The October 8 Revolutionary Movement of Brazil issued a 
statement on March 11 strongly urging the United States to 
immediately rescind the unreasonable preconditions and 
satisfactorily implement all the steps of simultaneous action 
according to the DPRK-U.S. agreed conclusions. 
  It also demanded that Japan and the South Korean authorities 
stop balking the DPRK-U.S. talks and promptly give up their 
nuclear arms development jeopardizing peace not only on the 
Korean peninsula but in Asia and the rest of the world. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

