<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 22 (KCNA) -- MINJU CHOSON dedicates 
a by-lined article to the independence of Namibia. 
  The article says: 
  Since the proclamation of the Republic the Namibian people 
have striven to build a new life, valiantly overcoming trials 
and difficulties that cropped up in their way. 
  Pursuing a non-aligned foreign policy, the Namibian 
Government is strengthening relations with many countries of the 
world and member states of the organization of African unity and 
fighting against imperialism and racism. 
  The Korean and the Namibian people established friendly 
bonds 
on the road of the common struggle for independence against 
imperialism. 
  Especially, the friendly and cooperative relations between 
the two countries have further developed since the establishment 
of diplomatic relations at ambassadorial level on March 22, 1990. 
  Believing that the relations between the two peoples will 
grow stronger and develop in different fields on the basis of 
the idea of independence, peace and friendship, the Korean 
people wish the Namibian people greater success in their 
strivings for the development and prosperity of the country. 

</TEXT>

