<H3> <TI>   KCNA Notes Increase in Railway Freight Tonnage </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2403062394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0424 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2403062394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 24 (KCNA) -- Railway workers in the 
DPRK keep effecting innovations. 
  The general bureaux of railways carried hundreds of 
thousands 
more tons of freight than their plan in recent one month. The 
transport turnover of the general bureau of Western railways was 
207,400 tons more than the assignment in the period. 
  The general bureau of Eastern railways and the Kaechon 
general bureau of railways hauled freight 20 to 30 percent more 
than the rated traction tonnage by scrupulously organizing and 
commanding transport and reducing the stoppage time of wagons. 
  Haeju Chongnyon, Unpit, Paechon and many other railway 
stations have hit their first-quarter assignments ahead of 
schedule. 

</TEXT>

